## Description {#details}

An <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/objectlayer">ObjectLayer</a> implementation built on JITLink.

Clients can use this class to add relocatable object files to an <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/executionsession">ExecutionSession</a>, and it typically serves as the base layer (underneath a compiling layer like <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/ircompilelayer">IRCompileLayer</a>) for the rest of the JIT.

Definition at line 41 of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/executionengine/include/llvm/executionengine/orc/objectlinkinglayer-h">ObjectLinkingLayer.h</a>.

### setReturnObjectBuffer() {#a4969d2212f78f895fc8184d5a9613387}

<MemberDefinition

  labels = {["inline"]}>
Set an object buffer return function.

By default object buffers are deleted once the JIT has linked them. If a return function is set then it will be called to transfer ownership of the buffer instead.
